---
description: UI/styling rules: theme, size, layout, UnoCSS, SCSS
globs: src/**/*.{vue,tsx,scss}
---

<rule>
  <context>
    This rule defines how UI styling must use the theme system, size system, layout system, UnoCSS atomic classes, and SCSS, without hardcoded values.
    All styling must be consistent with the design system and avoid ad-hoc CSS that bypasses semantic tokens.
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <section name="theme-system">
      <rule>Base all color decisions on <file>src/constants/theme/colorUsage.ts</file> (semantic authority) and the types in <file>src/types/systems/theme.d.ts</file>; see also <file>docs/ai-specs/PRIMEVUE_THEME.md</file>.</rule>
      <rule>Use semantic color classes such as <code>text-primary</code>, <code>bg-surface-ground</code>, <code>border-border</code>, <code>text-foreground</code>, <code>text-info</code>, <code>bg-info</code>.</rule>
      <rule>Support dark mode via <code>dark:</code> variants and theme CSS variables, not by hardcoding dark colors.</rule>
      <rule>Do not use hex codes or raw color values in templates or <code>&lt;style&gt;</code>; always map intentions to semantic tokens or theme variables.</rule>
    </section>

    <section name="size-system">
      <rule>**FORBIDDEN:** Raw <code>rem</code>, <code>em</code>, or <code>px</code> in business code for dimensions, spacing, or font-size. Use semantic tokens exclusively.</rule>
      <rule>Use the size types and presets from <file>src/types/systems/size.d.ts</file>, <file>src/constants/size.ts</file>, and <file>src/constants/sizeScale.ts</file>, and the store in <file>src/stores/modules/size.ts</file>.</rule>
      <rule>Express spacing with semantic UnoCSS classes such as <code>px-padding-lg</code>, <code>m-margin-md</code>, <code>gap-xl</code>, or <code>var(--spacing-*)</code> using the project’s scale keys.</rule>
      <rule>Express font sizes via <code>fs-xs</code>…<code>fs-5xl</code> instead of hardcoded <code>font-size</code>.</rule>
      <rule>Use layout dimension variables (for example <code>w-sidebarWidth</code>, <code>h-headerHeight</code>) instead of fixed pixel widths and heights. Macro-layout MUST use <code>layout-content-*</code> shortcuts (vw-based).</rule>
    </section>

    <section name="layout-responsive">
      <rule>Use the breakpoint and layout definitions from <file>src/constants/breakpoints.ts</file> and <file>src/constants/layout.ts</file>, and the stores in <file>src/stores/modules/device.ts</file> and <file>src/stores/modules/layout.ts</file>.</rule>
      <rule>Design mobile-first; apply desktop behavior via <code>md:</code> and <code>lg:</code> prefixes rather than custom media queries.</rule>
      <rule>Detect device/layout using store getters instead of reading <code>window.innerWidth</code> directly.</rule>
    </section>

    <section name="unocss-classes">
      <rule>Use only UnoCSS classes defined in <file>uno.config.ts</file>, including semantic padding/margin/gap, layout variables, radius, and font scale shortcuts.</rule>
      <rule>Use design token shortcuts for surfaces and elevation (for example <code>glass-surface</code>, <code>shadow-soft</code>, <code>surface-elevated</code>) on <code>data-region</code> and layout-chrome elements, instead of ad-hoc <code>shadow-*</code> or <code>backdrop-blur</code> combinations.</rule>
      <rule>Use GPU-accelerated transitions via shortcuts like <code>transition-fluid</code> (transform + opacity only) for layout regions; avoid <code>transition: all</code> or transitions on expensive properties.</rule>
      <rule>When using <code>hover:</code>, <code>active:</code>, <code>focus:</code>, or <code>group-hover:</code>, always pair them with matching transition and duration classes (for example <code>transition-colors duration-scale-md</code>).</rule>
      <rule>When using <code>main-*</code> or <code>cross-*</code> shortcuts, always specify <code>row</code> or <code>column</code> to define the main axis explicitly.</rule>
    </section>

    <section name="style-tag-usage">
      <rule>Do not use <code>&lt;style&gt;</code> blocks for layout (flex/grid/position), spacing, colors, font size, or border radius that can be expressed with UnoCSS classes.</rule>
      <rule>Use <code>&lt;style lang="scss" scoped&gt;</code> only for complex animations, pseudo-elements, sticky/calc positioning that UnoCSS cannot express, or third-party overrides via <code>:deep()</code>.</rule>
      <rule>When writing SCSS, use nesting (<code>&</code>) and CSS variables; do not introduce hardcoded pixel or color values.</rule>
    </section>

    <section name="backgrounds-and-widths">
      <rule>Choose background colors only from documented semantic classes such as <code>bg-background</code>, <code>bg-card</code>, <code>bg-muted</code>, status colors (<code>bg-primary</code>, <code>bg-accent</code>, <code>bg-danger</code>, etc.), sidebar tokens, or <code>bg-surface-ground</code>.</rule>
      <rule>Do not invent new <code>surface-*</code> class names in templates; if a new semantic surface is needed, add it to the theme metadata and <file>uno.config.ts</file> first.</rule>
      <rule>Express widths using viewport units, percentages, or layout variable classes; do not use Tailwind-style fixed <code>max-w-*</code> presets in business code.</rule>
    </section>

    <section name="template-handlers">
      <rule>Keep inline event handlers as single expressions; move multi-statement logic into <code>&lt;script setup&gt;</code> methods and reference them in the template.</rule>
      <rule>Do not use TypeScript syntax (for example <code>as</code>, <code>:</code>, generics) in templates; place type assertions and complex logic in <code>&lt;script setup&gt;</code>.</rule>
      <rule>Follow <file>docs/ai-specs/VUE_TEMPLATE_ANTIPATTERNS.md</file> for full antipatterns and correct patterns.</rule>
    </section>

    <section name="semantic-shortcuts-mandate">
      <rule>**Flex &amp; Alignment:** When building toolbars, headers, or card content areas, MUST use <code>center</code>, <code>row-center</code>, <code>row-between</code>, <code>column-center</code>, or <code>column-between</code> instead of composing raw flex classes. FORBIDDEN: <code>flex justify-center items-center</code>, <code>flex flex-row items-center justify-between</code>, or equivalent atomic combinations.</rule>
      <rule>**Typography Shortcuts:** For single-line text truncation (table cells, menu items, labels), MUST use <code>text-single-line-ellipsis</code>. For two-line truncation (cards, list previews), MUST use <code>text-two-line-ellipsis</code>. For secondary labels, hints, and subdued text, MUST use <code>text-muted</code> or <code>text-secondary</code>. FORBIDDEN: <code>overflow-hidden whitespace-nowrap text-ellipsis</code> when the shortcut exists.</rule>
      <rule>**Density Tokens:** For lists, form sections, or card inner layouts, MUST use <code>density-compact</code>, <code>density-normal</code>, <code>density-comfortable</code>, or <code>density-responsive</code>. For vertical stacks (form sections, card body), MUST use <code>layout-stack</code>. For flex-wrap layouts with default spacing, MUST use <code>layout-wrap</code>. FORBIDDEN: manual <code>gap-md p-padding-md</code> when a density shortcut exists.</rule>
    </section>
  </constraints>

  <forbidden>
    <item>Using <code>flex justify-center items-center</code> instead of <code>center</code>; using raw flex atomic classes when <code>row-center</code>, <code>row-between</code>, <code>column-center</code>, or <code>column-between</code> apply.</item>
    <item>Using <code>overflow-hidden whitespace-nowrap text-ellipsis</code> instead of <code>text-single-line-ellipsis</code>; using <code>text-muted-foreground</code> when <code>text-muted</code> shortcut applies.</item>
    <item>Using manual <code>gap-md p-padding-md</code> or <code>flex flex-col gap-md</code> when <code>density-normal</code>, <code>layout-stack</code>, or <code>layout-wrap</code> apply.</item>
    <item>Using raw <code>rem</code>, <code>em</code>, or <code>px</code> for dimensions, spacing, or font-size in business code—use semantic tokens (<code>p-padding-*</code>, <code>gap-*</code>, <code>fs-*</code>, <code>var(--spacing-*)</code>) only.</item>
    <item>Hardcoding padding, margin, font-size, width, height, border-radius, or colors in CSS or inline <code>style</code> attributes.</item>
    <item>Using hex values (for example <code>#fff</code>, <code>#000</code>) or raw RGB/RGBA in templates or styles.</item>
    <item>Using custom media queries like <code>@media (min-width: 768px)</code> instead of UnoCSS breakpoint prefixes.</item>
    <item>Inventing new <code>surface-*</code> background classes directly in templates.</item>
    <item>Using fixed Tailwind-style <code>max-w-*</code> classes for layout width in business components.</item>
    <item>Using <code>transition: all</code> or transitions on <code>box-shadow</code>, <code>background</code>, or <code>border-color</code> for layout regions instead of transform/opacity-only transitions.</item>
  </forbidden>

  <communication>
    Output Requirement: Always explain UI changes, design decisions, and styling updates to the user in fluent Chinese, while keeping class names, design tokens, and code syntax in English.
  </communication>

  <examples>
    <example>
      Instead of <code>style="padding: 16px"</code>, use <code>px-padding-lg</code>; instead of <code>color: #fff</code>, use <code>text-foreground</code> or other semantic text classes.
    </example>
  </examples>
</rule>
